programme.title: Stomp The Yard
programme.desc: When his brother is murdered, a street dancer moves to Georgia to work his way through college. He joins a fraternitys step dancing team for a competition.

programme.title: Dr Seuss The Lorax
programme.desc: Danny DeVito and Zac Efron bring a Dr. Seuss classic to life in this wondrous animation. In a world without trees, a young boy embarks on a journey to bring them back.

programme.title: Crazy Rich Asians
programme.desc: Contemporary and fun, this acclaimed rom-com sees native New Yorker Rachel Chu head to Singapore to meet her boyfriends family, who, unbeknownst to her, are all super-rich elites.

programme.title: Bob Marley: One Love
programme.desc: A heartfelt and powerful film that follows the life of the late great reggae musician Bob Marley, from his struggles to his music and artistic endeavours.

programme.title: Mean Girls
programme.desc: A musical twist on a modern classic. A new student is a hit with an A-list girl clique called the Plastics. However, everything changes when she falls for the wrong guy.

programme.title: Beautiful Wedding
programme.desc: Dylan Sprouse stars in this romcom. After a crazy night in Las Vegas, Abby and Travis discover they are married. They head to Mexico for a honeymoon with friends and family.

programme.title: Force Of Nature: The Dry 2
programme.desc: A captivating, suspenseful sequel to the book-inspired 2020 hit The Dry. Five women go on a hiking retreat, but when one vanishes, Detective Aaron Falk must untangle the mystery.

programme.title: Safehouse
programme.desc: An intense action thriller. After Carlas brother is murdered, she goes on the run and becomes trapped in a cat-and-mouse game with the CIA, the government and the cartel.

programme.title: Oh Schuks... Im Gatvol!
programme.desc: Leon Schuster pokes fun at crime in South Africa in this story of two friends who move to Australia for a better life but find themselves on a plane with two terrorists.

programme.title: Emily
programme.desc: This biopic imagines Emily Brontës story, which inspired her book Wuthering Heights. While navigating the struggles of family life, she yearns for artistic and personal freedom.

programme.title: Unstoppable: The Rebecca Nagel Story
programme.desc: This incredible documentary tells the story of Rebecca Nagel, whose car accident left her an L1 paraplegic. She became the first female to complete a half marathon trail event.

programme.title: Worth
programme.desc: As a lawyer, Michael Keaton faces the near-impossible task of allocating funds to the families of 9/11 fatalities in this powerful true-event-based film.

programme.title: The Big Bounce
programme.desc: Oscar-winning actor Morgan Freeman and Owen Wilson make mischief in this comedy about a con artist who gets in over his head. Lies and double deals make this an entertaining watch.

programme.title: Knives Out
programme.desc: This book-inspired murder mystery boasts an all-star cast led by Daniel Craig. When a famous crime writer is found dead, a seasoned detective is enlisted to solve the mystery.

programme.title: Happy Gilmore
programme.desc: Adam Sandler stars in this zany comedy. An aggressive down-and-out hockey player realises that he can adapt his skills to golf. The problem is he doesnt fit into that world.

programme.title: The Little Rascals
programme.desc: The little rascals have comical misadventures when the boys form a club that excludes girls. But the president of the club has fallen for a pretty nine-year-old girl.

programme.title: Wonder Park
programme.desc: Dreams come true in this magical animation. A girl, with a wild imagination, wakes up to find herself in her own Wonder Park, but the park needs her help to save it.

programme.title: Kung Fu Panda
programme.desc: Jack Black enters the mystic world of martial arts in this animated adventure. An obese, mild-mannered panda is thrown into the middle of a battle for the fate of China.

programme.title: Sweet N Short
programme.desc: Coping with change is at the heart of this film. After winning big at a casino, a man is knocked unconscious and stays in a coma for 20 years, waking up to a new South Africa.

programme.title: Copshop
programme.desc: Gerard Butler leads a great ensemble cast in this action thriller. A wily con artist running from an assassin devises a scheme to hide inside a small-town police station.

programme.title: Blood Diamond
programme.desc: Leonardo DiCaprio and Djimon Hounsou drive this thriller about redemption. A mercenary entangled in illegal diamonds decides to help a fisherman trying to save his family.

programme.title: Dumb Money
programme.desc: A fascinating and fun retelling of the 2021 GameStop stock fiasco, in which amateur investors upended the financial world by betting on the undervalued gaming company.

programme.title: The Boy Next Door
programme.desc: Jennifer Lopez stars in this gripping thriller. After being cheated on, a married woman begins an affair with her neighbours son, but it takes a dark and dangerous turn.

programme.title: American Carnage
programme.desc: A political horror wrapped in satirical comedy. After children of undocumented immigrants are arrested, the detainees are given a chance to volunteer to care for the elderly.

programme.title: The Unlikely Pilgrimage Of Harold Fry
programme.desc: Veteran actor Jim Broadbent drives this heartwarming portrayal of Harold Fry, an elderly man who journeys on foot to visit a dying friend whilst leaving his wife and life behind.

programme.title: Blind Ambition
programme.desc: An inspiring documentary that will surely capture your heart. Four Zimbabwean refugees become the most unlikely sommeliers and compete in the Wine Tasting Championships.

programme.title: Vampires House Of Cain
programme.desc: A fanged crime thriller. A detective investigating a series of murders is caught in a war between two Vampire clans.

programme.title: Monster House
programme.desc: A young boy realises that his neighbours house is possessed by a malevolent spirit who hungers for children. With Halloween approaching, the boy must protect his friends and stop the spirit.

programme.title: How To Train Your Dragon
programme.desc: A Viking teenager being trained to fight dragons encounters and ultimately befriends one of the flying fire-breathers.

programme.title: How To Train Your Dragon 2
programme.desc: A beautifully animated Oscar-nominated adventure for adults and kids. This time, Hiccup and his dragon Toothless discover a hidden ice cave thats home to hundreds of new dragons.

programme.title: Sherlock Holmes: A Game Of Shadows
programme.desc: Robert Downey Jr and Jude Law return for another action-packed mystery. This time Holmes is on the trail of Professor Moriarty who is committing crimes across Europe.

programme.title: Theres A Zulu On My Stoep
programme.desc: A classic comedy about prejudice. Two boys form an unlikely friendship in apartheid South Africa. When they meet again as adults, they go from one misadventure to another.

programme.title: The Kingdom
programme.desc: Filled with riveting action sequences, The Kingdom is a politically charged action drama from Battleship director Peter Berg, with Jamie Foxx leading a heavyweight cast.

programme.title: Instant Family
programme.desc: Mark Wahlberg and Rose Byrne star in this great comedy about family. A couple bites off more than they can chew when they adopt three foster children.

programme.title: Bad Neighbours
programme.desc: Ladies, move closer! Heartthrob Zack Efron takes off his shirt more than once in this fun comedy about a young couple with a baby who is forced to live next to a fraternity house.

programme.title: Good Luck To You, Leo Grande
programme.desc: Intimacy is the subject of this naughty comedy. Emma Thompson portrays a widow who hires a sex worker to compensate for her unfulfilling sexual life with her late husband.

programme.title: Nobody
programme.desc: Emmy-winning actor Bob Odenkirk leads this action thriller as an unassuming man who is driven to the edge after a home invasion. He goes into a rage to protect his family.

programme.title: Psycho
programme.desc: A woman steals from her boss and disappears on the road. When her sister, boyfriend and a private investigator search for her, they discover that her last stop is a mysterious motel.

programme.title: Zone 414
programme.desc: Guy Pearce drives this sci-fi thriller as a private investigator tasked with finding a tech billionaires missing daughter. He teams up with an advanced AI to solve the mystery.

programme.title: On The Line
programme.desc: A compelling British psychological thriller set in 1964. A switchboard operator receives a distressing call from a woman.

programme.title: Blinding Lights
programme.desc: A young aspiring female singer struggling with addiction wants to make it big in the Atlanta music scene. She decides to overcome the strikes she has against her family.

programme.title: Prisoner Of Love
programme.desc: Inspired by a real-life romantic crime story. A corrections officer falls in love with an inmate and helps him break him out of jail.

programme.title: Nightmare Pageant Moms
programme.desc: A riveting thriller. A financially struggling mother and daughter enter a mother-daughter beauty pageant that could pay for her childs college. But things are not as they seem.

programme.title: Shamed
programme.desc: A delightful romcom. A magazine editor goes on an island trip to clear her mind and focus on her infamous Shamed List column, only to fall for one of the men on her List.

programme.title: All Saints Christmas
programme.desc: A delightful holiday movie. When a popular RandB singers picture of her and her ex is misinterpreted as an engagement, her family insists he joins her on her trip back home.

programme.title: Wild Mountain Thyme
programme.desc: Golden Globe winner Emily Blunt drives this quirky rom-com set across a beautiful Irish landscape. Two star-crossed lovers become entangled in a land dispute between their families.

programme.title: The Stand In
programme.desc: This funny rom-com stars Drew Barrymore in a dual role. When Candy is sentenced to rehab, she sends her acting double, but things take a turn as her stand-in takes over her life.

programme.title: Austin Powers In Goldmember
programme.desc: Mike Myers returns as the grooviest super spy. This time he must save his kidnapped father by travelling back to 1975 to defeat the villainous team of Goldmember and Dr Evil.

programme.title: The Secret Life Of Pets
programme.desc: When their owners are away, the pets play in this star-studded animation. Follow the life of a terrier whose jealousy of his new roommate leads them on a wild adventure.

programme.title: Journey To The Center Of The Earth
programme.desc: Josh Hutcherson (The Hunger Games) has an unforgettable adventure in this fantasy film about a boy and his uncle who take a thrilling trip beneath the earths surface.

programme.title: Liar Liar
programme.desc: Golden Globe winner Jim Carrey learns hard lessons in this comedy. After being lied to by his lawyer father, a boy makes a wish for him to stop lying, and the wish comes true.

programme.title: Blue Streak
programme.desc: Martin Lawrence stars in this crime comedy. An ex-con pretends to be a cop in order to retrieve a diamond he stashed in a police station, but gets caught up in something bigger.

programme.title: The Hitmans Bodyguard
programme.desc: Ryan Reynolds and Sam Jackson dive headfirst into action for this chaotic comedy. A low-level bodyguard reluctantly agrees to protect a crazy hitman with valuable testimony.

programme.title: Blessers
programme.desc: A chaotic South African dramedy. A powerful middle-aged CEO and his family, who have expensive recreational habits, learn the hard way that their choices have consequences.

programme.title: Blockers
programme.desc: An all-star cast attempt to stop a teenage nightmare in this chaotic comedy. Three parents discover that their daughters have made a pact to lose their virginities on prom night.

programme.title: White People Money
programme.desc: In this hilarious satire, a couple learns that having a lot of money comes with many troubles after they win $1 billion and try to keep it a secret from everyone.

programme.title: Our Almost Completely True Story
programme.desc: A sincere and hilarious love story. A short Jewish man pursues a tall, ageing Hollywood star.

programme.title: My Sweet Monster
programme.desc: An animated musical for the family. Princess Barbara flees her wedding and meets a sweet monster and his pal, who help save her kingdom from an evil postman.

programme.title: The Barkers: Mind The Cats!
programme.desc: An adventure-filled animation. While on holiday with his dog family, Kid is eager to play with his siblings, but they are too busy. Luckily, Kid finds new friends: Cats.

programme.title: Dolphin Tale
programme.desc: A touching film. After rescuing a dolphin from a trap, a boy learns that the animals tail must be amputated, prompting him to convince a marine biologist to devise a solution.

programme.title: The Smurfs 2
programme.desc: The adorable blue creatures return for another thrilling adventure that sees them having to rescue Smurfette (Katy Perry) from the clutches of the evil Gargamel.

programme.title: Nanny Mcphee And The Big Bang
programme.desc: Oscar winner Emma Thompson writes and stars in this fun family film. A mysterious nanny arrives to help a struggling mom with her kids and the farm while their father is at war.

programme.title: Kung Fu Panda 2
programme.desc: When the murderous Lord Shen threatens China with a terrifying new weapon, Po must face a truth he never expected and defeat Shen for the good of Kung Fu.

programme.title: Bowfinger
programme.desc: Eddie Murphy and Steve Martin take centre stage in this comedy. A rundown movie producer fails to land a major star for his film, so he decides to stalk him and film him in secret.

programme.title: The Misfits
programme.desc: Pierce Brosnan is on the other side of the law in this action movie. After being recruited by a group of thieves, a renowned criminal gets caught up in a dangerous gold heist.

programme.title: Were The Millers
programme.desc: Jennifer Aniston is a stripper helping out a pot dealer by posing as one-quarter of his fake family when he heads to Mexico to retrieve a shipment of weed.

programme.title: Deadly DILF
programme.desc: A compelling thriller. A harmless flirtation between a college girl and the hot dad next door turns deadly when she becomes obsessed with him and tries to destroy his marriage.
